{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 08:35:48.064679", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nSummary\n- Overall OSPF control plane and core/distribution/server routing appear healthy.\n- One access host (host_2_1_1_1) exhibits a clear L3 misconfiguration that prevents any off-subnet connectivity, impacting its ability to reach DNS and the load balancer/web services.\n- Other host (host_1_1_1_1) demonstrates normal end-to-end service reachability to DNS and the HTTP load balancer, and OSPF propagation across routers is consistent with design.\n\nKey Observations and Tests\n1) End-to-end reachability\n- host_1_1_1_1 → 10.200.0.7 (load_balancer): OK (0% loss, RTT ~2–4 ms).\n- Multiple servers → host_1_1_1_1: OK.\n- host_2_1_1_1 → load_balancer (10.200.0.7), DNS (10.200.0.2), host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.10): Fails with “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.2.1.10.\n\n2) HTTP service tests\n- host_1_1_1_1 curl http://web99.local (load balancer): Consistently successful (total ~1.1–1.3 s), indicating working DNS resolution and HTTP path.\n- host_1_1_1_1 curl http://10.200.0.3 (web_server_0): Successful, consistent with availability of named Apache servers (web0.local…web3.local).\n- host_2_1_1_1 curl http://web99.local: Intermittent timeouts (~4–5 s totals) with only occasional successes, consistent with inability to reliably reach DNS and/or the server farm due to L3 default-route issue (see below).\n\n3) Host network configurations\n- host_1_1_1_1:\n  - IP: 10.1.1.10/24 (dynamic)\n  - Default gateway: 10.1.1.1\n  - Behavior: Normal; DHCP lease present; broadcast set correctly; full reachability.\n\n- host_2_1_1_1:\n  - IP: 10.2.1.10/24\n  - Default gateway: 10.2.1.254 (incorrect)\n  - ARP: 10.2.1.254 INCOMPLETE; 10.2.1.1 REACHABLE\n  - Ping 10.2.1.1 (local default gateway IP on router): OK\n  - Ping default route 10.2.1.254: Fails\n  - Behavior: All off-subnet traffic fails (DNS, server farm, other host subnets), as replies are attempted via a nonexistent next-hop.\n\n4) Distribution and server routing state (OSPF/forwarding)\n- router_dist_2_1 (10.2.1.1/24 on br0):\n  - OSPF routes present to 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.200.0.0/24 via core (172.16.0.8), and connected 10.2.1.0/24 on br0: Correct.\n- router_dist_1_1 (10.1.1.1/24 on br0):\n  - Connected 10.1.1.0/24 and OSPF routes to 10.2.1.0/24 and 10.200.0.0/24 via core (172.16.0.6): Correct.\n- server_access_router:\n  - 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected; OSPF routes to 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 via core (172.16.0.10): Correct.\n- Conclusion: OSPF adjacencies and route propagation across server-access and distribution layers are consistent and healthy.\n\n5) DHCP configuration\n- dhcp_server dhcpd.conf:\n  - Subnet 10.2.1.0/24 specifies option routers 10.2.1.1 and DNS 10.200.0.2 (correct).\n  - Host_2’s ip addr output lacks “dynamic” flag and shows an incorrect default route (10.2.1.254), suggesting it is likely not using DHCP correctly and/or has static/misconfigured default gateway.\n\nAnomalies Detected\n- host_2_1_1_1 default gateway incorrectly set to 10.2.1.254; ARP unresolved for that next-hop.\n- Resulting symptoms:\n  - No off-subnet reachability from host_2_1_1_1 (to DNS, load balancer, other subnets).\n  - Intermittent/failed HTTP lookups to web99.local due to unreachable DNS and server farm.\n- Scope appears limited to host_2_1_1_1; the rest of the network (routing, server farm services, DNS, load balancer) is functioning as expected.\n\nFault Localization\n- Fault localized to the endpoint host: host_2_1_1_1 (its local routing configuration).\n- Access L2 path is fine (host_2_1_1_1 can ping 10.2.1.1 and has ARP for the router’s MAC).\n- Distribution router, core, and server-access router are not implicated; OSPF and routes are correct.\n\nLikely Root Cause\n- Misconfiguration of host_2_1_1_1’s default route (set to 10.2.1.254 instead of 10.2.1.1).\n- Given DHCP server advertises the correct default gateway (10.2.1.1), host_2_1_1_1 likely did not receive/apply the DHCP lease properly or is using static/manual network settings inconsistent with the site design.\n\nImpact Assessment\n- host_1_1_1_1: Normal operation; end-to-end access to DNS and HTTP services via the load balancer is healthy.\n- host_2_1_1_1: Unable to reach DNS/load balancer/server farm; user on this subnet/host would experience broken name resolution and web service access.\n- Infrastructure: OSPF and routed connectivity between server farm and distribution/core layers is normal. No systemic faults observed.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10976, "output_tokens": 5658, "total_tokens": 16634, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4608}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4288}}}
